'''Ramón Alcaraz''' was an officer in the [[Mexican Army]] who wrote many books about the [[Mexican–American War]], including 1848's ''Apuntes para la historia de la guerra entre México y los Estados Unidos'' (which in 1850 [[Albert Ramsey|Albert C. Ramsey]] translated into English as ''The Other Side, or: Notes for the History of the War Between Mexico and the United States, Written in Mexico'').<ref>Ramón Alcaraz, et al. ''The Other Side, or: Notes for the History of the War Between Mexico and the United States, Written in Mexico''. New York: Burt Franklin 1850; republished 1970.</ref>

